1. What is the difference between getElementById, getElementsByClassName, and querySelector / querySelectorAll? ==> 

Ans: => 1
    the difference between getElementById & getElementsByClassName is 
    1.getElementById is specific single  elements selecting method which is get by using getElementById
    2.getElementsByClassName is multiple elements selecting method.
    3.querySelector is as like as id type, for single elements .selector
    4.querySelectorAll is provide full dom you can access multiple things using selector
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. How do you create and insert a new element into the DOM? ==>

Ans: ==> 2
    At first get an existing element as a parent , 
        then create a new element {div or li or a or section etc} with variable
            then get parent.appendChild(variable);
    Done!
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. What is Event Bubbling? And how does it work? ==>

Ans: ==> 3
    Event Bubbling is a like one way wave, when its happened its passing from child to parent elements then parent to grand-parent elements.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. What is Event Delegation in JavaScript? Why is it useful? ==>

Ans: ==>
    Event Delegation is parent.evenListener. who control his child elements thru event Bubbling,
    its can add new element without adding new (add.EventListener), also can catch element using event.target, & its dynamic also,
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5. What is the difference between preventDefault() and stopPropagation() methods? ==>

Ans: ==>
    preventDefault() is switch-off all kind of default browsing activity,like page reloading etc
    stopPropagation() is kind of Opposite but its one thing is stop event Bubbling,
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------